<TITLE> Toll in Pakistan hotel blast rises to 52 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Islamabad, Sep 21 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Searchers combing through the burnt shell of the Marriott Hotel in Pakistan's capital found more bodies the morning after a suicide bomb attack, bringing the death toll to 52, a senior government official said on Sunday. An American and a German were killed, while at least 13 other foreigners were among the 271 wounded in the devasting blast, Rehman Malik, the top official in the Interior Ministry, told Reuters
